The term "Mujaddid" (Verified Reformer) is a venerable term for Muslims and no mainstream scholar has ever referred to Muhammad Abduh as being a Mujaddid. The reason for the veneration is that this title goes to one man per century and was given by the Prophet of Islam 1400+ years ago. The fact that he is referred to as such in a book written by a non-Muslim historian should not be presented in this misleading manner (as part of his introduction).
